WEBVTT

00:02.669 --> 00:05.171
HOUSEMATES,
REPORT TO THE BACKYARD.

00:05.255 --> 00:07.132
{\an1}Foxxy: THE PRODUCERS SET UP
A BADMINTON CHALLENGE

00:07.215 --> 00:09.926
{\an1}BETWEEN US AND THE ORIGINAL
CAST OF <i> DRAWN TOGETHER.</i>

00:10.009 --> 00:14.097
{\an1}PREPARED TO BE TRANSFORMED
INTO A BUNCH OF LOSERS.

00:14.180 --> 00:17.434
{\an5}ALL RIGHT, TEAM,
LET'S MAKE THESE GUYS
EAT SHUTTLECOCK.

00:17.517 --> 00:20.019
{\an1}HEY, CAN WE GET
THIS GAME GOING ALREADY?

00:20.103 --> 00:21.354
All: READY!

00:33.366 --> 00:34.409
I GOT IT! ALL MINE!

00:34.492 --> 00:36.619
OOH!

00:36.703 --> 00:38.538
{\an1}INTERFERENCE.
XANDIR WAS TOTALLY OFFSIDES.

00:38.621 --> 00:41.875
DO OVER. [GRUNTS]

00:47.422 --> 00:49.924
DUDE, YOU'RE THE WORST
ATHLETE I'VE EVER SEEN,

00:50.008 --> 00:52.719
AND I'VE BEEN TO, LIKE,
EVERY SPECIAL OLYMPICS.

00:52.802 --> 00:56.222
{\an5}THERE'S THIS ONE GUY,
BASICALLY JUST A HEAD
ON A SPRING,

00:56.306 --> 00:57.098
AND HE'S WAY
BETTER THAN YOU.

00:57.182 --> 01:01.561
{\an1}I CAN'T HELP IT.
I CAN'T DO SPORTS, OK?

01:01.644 --> 01:02.812
{\an1}THERE. NOW YOU KNOW
MY KRYPTONITE--

01:02.896 --> 01:05.648
DOING SPORTS GAMES.

01:05.732 --> 01:08.067
ARE YOU HAPPY?
I HATE YOU ALL.

01:08.151 --> 01:11.654
[SOBBING]

01:11.738 --> 01:14.532
PROCEED TO MAIN
TITLE SEQUENCE.

01:29.631 --> 01:30.757
AH!

01:30.840 --> 01:32.675
I SUCK.

01:32.759 --> 01:34.010
KEEP 'EM COMING.

01:34.093 --> 01:37.597
I THINK YOU'VE HAD
ENOUGH LEMONADE, MISTER.

01:37.680 --> 01:40.350
{\an1}I'LL TELL YOU WHEN I'VE HAD
ENOUGH LEMONADE, MISTER.

01:40.433 --> 01:42.685
JUST GIVE ME
THE WHOLE DAMN LEMON.

01:44.437 --> 01:46.314
[GRUNTS]

01:47.607 --> 01:50.527
MMMMMMMMM! GG!

01:50.610 --> 01:52.737
HEY, WOOLDOOR, JUMP ON.

01:52.821 --> 01:54.823
LET'S GO DO SOMETHING COOL.

01:54.906 --> 01:56.032
I CAN'T, SPANKY. IT'S SUNDAY.

01:56.115 --> 01:59.285
{\an1}YOU KNOW, MY SPECIAL DAY
TO MAKE LEMONADE

01:59.369 --> 02:01.079
WITH MY BESTEST
FRIEND CLARA.

02:01.162 --> 02:04.499
{\an1}WELL, UNLESS YOU'RE
MAKING LEMONADE <i> ON</i> CLARA,

02:04.582 --> 02:06.000
THAT'S NOTHING SPECIAL.

02:06.084 --> 02:06.543
{\an3}HMM.

02:06.626 --> 02:08.377
{\an1}YOO-HOO!

02:08.461 --> 02:10.713
HMM.

02:10.797 --> 02:12.966
OK, SPANKY.

02:13.049 --> 02:14.342
LET'S GO.

02:14.425 --> 02:17.595
WE'RE OFF TO THE COOLEST
PLACE IN ALL THE LAND--

02:17.679 --> 02:18.888
{\an1}THE MALL.

02:18.972 --> 02:21.724
OH, YOU'RE BEAUTIFUL.

02:21.808 --> 02:22.600
WHAT'S YOUR NAME, MISTER?

02:22.684 --> 02:24.394
OH, PLEASE.

02:24.477 --> 02:28.731
{\an5}I ONLY CHAT
WITH REAL MEN WHO KNOW
HOW TO PLAY SPORTS.

02:28.815 --> 02:31.276
{\an1}[SOBBING]

02:31.359 --> 02:32.902
SHREK 2 WAS RIGHT.

02:32.986 --> 02:35.655
WHAT KIND OF MAN IS BAD
AT DOING SPORTS GAMES?

02:35.738 --> 02:39.492
{\an4}OH, LORD, IF THERE
IS A SPORT OUT THERE
THAT I CAN MASTER,

02:39.576 --> 02:41.369
PLEASE GIVE ME A SIGN.

02:41.452 --> 02:43.413
HEY, Y'ALL, WHO WANTS
TO SPONSOR ME?

02:43.496 --> 02:44.664
I'M WALKING IN
THE AIDS WALK NEXT WEEK.

02:44.747 --> 02:46.958
IT'S PER MILE.

02:47.041 --> 02:47.959
WALK? I CAN WALK.

02:48.042 --> 02:51.546
SO YOU ARE GONNA
SPONSOR ME?

02:51.629 --> 02:53.506
YOU KNOW IT'S
PER MILE, RIGHT?

02:53.590 --> 02:56.593
HELLS, NO, I WON'T
BE SPONSORING YOU.

02:56.676 --> 03:00.597
I'LL BE SPONSORING ME
TO WIN THE AIDS WALK.

03:00.680 --> 03:04.142
THE AIDS WALK IS NOT
COMPETITION, ASSHOLE.

03:04.225 --> 03:06.936
IT'S A CHARITY, LIKE NOT
SPITTING ON UGLY PEOPLE.

03:07.020 --> 03:09.272
I GAVE AT THE OFFICE.

03:09.355 --> 03:11.608
I'LL PRACTICE
NIGHT AND DAY.

03:11.691 --> 03:15.403
{\an5}BEFORE YOU KNOW IT,
I'LL DO MORE WALKING
AND HAVE MORE AIDS

03:15.486 --> 03:18.072
THAN YOU CAN
POSSIBLY IMAGINE.

03:18.156 --> 03:20.241
YOU WERE RIGHT, SPANKY.

03:20.325 --> 03:23.286
{\an1}THIS IS SO MUCH COOLER
THAN DOING A LEMONADE STAND.

03:23.369 --> 03:26.456
{\an1}BUT I DON'T HAVE ANY MONEY
TO BUY THIS CANDY.

03:26.539 --> 03:29.417
IF YOU WERE REALLY COOL,
YOU'D JUST STEAL IT.

03:29.500 --> 03:30.710
I CAN'T DO THAT.

03:29.500 --> 03:30.710
{\an3}WHY NOT?

03:30.793 --> 03:32.962
{\an4}'CAUSE I'M RIGHT HERE
AND I CAN HEAR
EVERYTHING YOU'RE SAYING.

03:33.046 --> 03:35.381
DON'T LISTEN
TO HER, WOOLDOOR.

03:35.465 --> 03:37.717
{\an5}JUST SLIP THE BAG
UNDER YOUR SHIRT
AND WALK OUT.

03:37.800 --> 03:38.885
SHE'LL NEVER KNOW.

03:38.968 --> 03:40.428
YES, I WILL.

03:40.511 --> 03:42.472
{\an1}AND SO WILL
THE SECURITY GUARD.

03:42.555 --> 03:43.973
HEY, HOW YOU DOING, FELLA?

03:44.057 --> 03:46.142
WHO ARE YOU GONNA
LISTEN TO, WOOLDOOR?

03:46.225 --> 03:47.810
ME, YOUR COOL FRIEND,

03:47.894 --> 03:50.313
OR SOME FILTHY WHORE
OFF THE STREET?

03:50.396 --> 03:51.940
I DIDN'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

03:52.023 --> 03:54.359
{\an1}I'VE NEVER STOLEN
ANYTHING IN MY LIFE.

03:54.442 --> 03:55.276
BUT SPANKY WAS PRETTY COOL,

03:55.360 --> 03:58.196
{\an1}AND SHE WAS
A FILTHY, FILTHY WHORE.

04:04.035 --> 04:05.745
[SOBBING]

04:05.828 --> 04:08.373
{\an3}[SIGHS]

04:09.749 --> 04:13.753
{\an1}[SOBBING]

04:22.428 --> 04:23.429
IT'S OVER.

04:23.513 --> 04:25.682
{\an1}JUST DROP THE CANDY AND
STEP AWAY FROM THE LEDGE.

04:25.765 --> 04:29.477
{\an1}PLEASE, MISTER.
I DIDN'T MEAN TO DO IT.

04:29.560 --> 04:30.645
I DON'T CARE.

04:30.728 --> 04:33.773
{\an1}I'M TELLING YOU, STEP AWAY
OR THE BITCH GETS IT!

04:33.856 --> 04:35.775
NO! DON'T DO IT!

04:35.858 --> 04:38.236
I'M NOT GONNA SAY IT AGAIN!

04:38.319 --> 04:41.030
RUN! HE'S GONNA KILL ME
NO MATTER WHAT YOU DO.

04:41.114 --> 04:43.658
{\an1}NO, NO, NO.
DON'T DO IT. I GIVE UP.

04:45.284 --> 04:46.828
UH! [SOBBING]

04:46.911 --> 04:49.372
TAKE HIM AWAY.

04:49.455 --> 04:53.459
AND NOW TO TIE UP
SOME LOOSE ENDS.

04:56.087 --> 04:57.130
[GUNSHOT]

04:57.213 --> 04:59.007
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

05:00.633 --> 05:03.219
{\an1}I DON'T KNOW
HOW LONG I WAS TRAPPED

05:03.302 --> 05:05.847
{\an1}IN THAT MALL SECURITY-SLASH-
LOST AND FOUND LOUNGE.

05:05.930 --> 05:09.267
{\an1}IT COULD'VE BEEN 1 MINUTE.
IT COULD'VE BEEN 10.

05:09.350 --> 05:11.185
OH. OOH.

05:11.269 --> 05:13.354
[CRUNCHING]

05:13.438 --> 05:15.732
{\an1}HEY, YOU, UH,
WOOLDOOR SOCKBAT?

05:15.815 --> 05:17.358
YES, MISTER.

05:17.442 --> 05:18.735
SIGN HERE AND YOU CAN GO.

05:18.818 --> 05:23.281
{\an1}GO? YOU MEAN...
I'M BEING LET OUT ALREADY?

05:23.364 --> 05:25.700
WELL, SURE. ALL YOU DID
WAS STEAL SOME CANDY.

05:25.783 --> 05:29.370
{\an4}IT'S NOT LIKE YOU CHEWED OFF
SOMEONE'S ARM, TESTICLES,
AND PART OF THEIR FACE.

05:30.830 --> 05:32.665
GEORGE, LET HIM OUT.

05:32.749 --> 05:34.834
OK, YOU'RE FREE TO GO.

05:36.169 --> 05:38.087
HEY, SOCKBAT,
OUT OF MY WAY.

05:38.171 --> 05:39.297
MAIN STORY COMING THROUGH.

05:39.380 --> 05:41.841
THE AIDS WALK
WAS DRAWING NEAR,

05:41.924 --> 05:45.261
{\an1}AND I WAS DETERMINED
TO BRING HOME THE GOLD.

05:45.344 --> 05:47.055
SO I JOINED THE MOST
ELITE WALKING FORCE

05:47.138 --> 05:49.515
IN THE FREE WORLD--

05:49.599 --> 05:51.267
THE MALL WALKERS.

05:51.350 --> 05:53.936
WOW. YOU GUYS ARE GOOD.

05:54.020 --> 05:55.313
{\an1}I MEAN LIKE "5-TIME
WORLD-WALKING CHAMPION

05:55.396 --> 05:57.857
{\an1}JOSE 'DADDY LONG LEGS'
MARTINEZ" GOOD.

05:57.940 --> 05:59.942
{\an1}WATCH OUT!

06:00.026 --> 06:00.651
YOU SHOULD GO
PLAY BADMINTON.

06:00.735 --> 06:02.737
{\an1}GO BACK TO JOGGING,
YOU HOMO.

06:02.820 --> 06:04.280
OH. OK, YOU GUYS
GO ON AHEAD.

06:04.363 --> 06:07.533
I SUCKED AT ALL
SPORTS GAMES,

06:07.617 --> 06:09.285
EVEN WALKING.

06:09.368 --> 06:11.287
{\an1}THERE WAS NO WAY
I COULD WIN THE AIDS WALK.

06:11.370 --> 06:14.957
{\an1}BUT THEN I SAW SOMETHING
THAT GAVE ME AN IDEA.

06:16.709 --> 06:20.046
{\an5}HEY THERE, BUB.
I NEED THE STRONGEST
STUFF YOU'VE GOT.

06:20.129 --> 06:22.340
{\an1}WELL, SIR, WE'VE GOT A TERRIFIC
LINE OF HERBAL SUPPLEMENTS.

06:22.423 --> 06:25.885
HERBAL? WHAT DO
I LOOK LIKE TO YOU?

06:25.968 --> 06:28.262
{\an1}SOME CRAZY WACKO WHO'LL PUT
ANYTHING INSIDE HIS BODY

06:28.346 --> 06:30.264
AND THEN TAKE PICTURES
OF IT COMING OUT

06:30.348 --> 06:31.641
AND POST THEM
ON HIS WEB SITE

06:31.724 --> 06:35.645
{\an5}WHICH GETS OVER
10,000 HITS A DAY,
MOST OF THEM IN GERMANY?

06:35.728 --> 06:37.146
DO I? DO I?

06:37.230 --> 06:39.941
{\an1}THEN I GUESS YOU WOULDN'T
BE INTERESTED IN, UH,

06:40.024 --> 06:41.776
STEROIDS.

06:41.859 --> 06:44.403
OH, I LIKE
TO WHISPER, TOO.

06:44.487 --> 06:47.156
{\an5}MY ONLY PROBLEM IS,
I NEVER KNOW
WHAT TO WHISPER.

06:47.240 --> 06:49.826
SO SOMETIMES I JUST
PRETEND, LIKE THIS.

06:49.909 --> 06:52.912
PSST-PSS-PSST-PSS.
PSS-PSST-PSS-PSST.

06:52.995 --> 06:56.040
{\an1}UM...UH, I'M GONNA
TAKE THAT AS A "YES."

06:56.124 --> 06:58.292
PLEASE, SIR, WALK THIS WAY.

06:58.376 --> 07:01.170
IF I COULD WALK THAT WAY,
I WOULDN'T NEED STEROIDS.

07:01.254 --> 07:02.004
{\an1}BOO!

07:02.088 --> 07:05.091
DEAR FELLAS,

07:05.174 --> 07:08.928
{\an1}I CAN'T BELIEVE HOW FAST
THINGS MOVE ON THE OUTSIDE.

07:10.847 --> 07:13.224
{\an1}I SAW AN AUTOMOBILE ONCE
WHEN I WAS A KID,

07:13.307 --> 07:14.016
{\an1}BUT NOW
THEY'RE EVERYWHERE.

07:14.100 --> 07:15.560
[GASPS]

07:17.436 --> 07:19.480
AAH!

07:19.564 --> 07:21.149
AAH!

07:21.232 --> 07:21.816
AAH!

07:21.899 --> 07:24.152
AAH!

07:24.235 --> 07:25.528
[ROOSTER CROWING]

07:25.611 --> 07:30.158
{\an1}THE WORLD WENT AND GOT ITSELF
IN A BIG DAMN HURRY.

07:30.241 --> 07:31.284
THE PAROLE BOARD
GOT ME A JOB

07:31.367 --> 07:34.245
BAGGING GROCERIES
AT THE FOODWAY.

07:34.328 --> 07:35.288
{\an1}IT'S HARD WORK,
AND I TRY TO KEEP UP,

07:35.371 --> 07:38.457
BUT MY HANDS HURT
MOST OF THE TIME.

07:38.541 --> 07:41.043
{\an1}I DON'T THINK THE STORE
MANAGER LIKES ME VERY MUCH.

07:41.127 --> 07:44.255
{\an1}HEY, UH, BOSS,
CAN I GO TO THE POTTY? PLEASE.

07:44.338 --> 07:46.674
HOW MANY TIMES
DO I HAVE TO TELL YOU?

07:46.757 --> 07:48.551
YOU AIN'T GOT TO ASK ME.

07:48.634 --> 07:51.679
{\an1}MAYBE AN HOUR
IN THE HOLE WILL TEACH YOU.

07:51.762 --> 07:55.224
{\an1}LIFE ON THE OUTSIDE
IS JUST TOO MUCH TO HANDLE.

07:55.308 --> 07:57.393
{\an1}I WISH THERE WAS SOMETHING
I COULD GRAB ON TO

07:57.476 --> 08:00.188
{\an5}SO THINGS COULD BE
LIKE THEY WERE
BEFORE I WENT AWAY.

08:02.565 --> 08:05.109
{\an4}THE WAY THEY
WERE WITH CLARA
AND OUR LEMONADE STAND.

08:05.193 --> 08:08.738
{\an4}WHY DID YOU GIVE HIM MONEY?
YOU KNOW HE'S JUST
GONNA SPEND IT ON LEMONADE.

08:11.115 --> 08:14.952
{\an4}I STARTED TRAINING
WITH MY NEW WORKOUT
PARTNER, MR. STEROIDS.

08:27.340 --> 08:30.051
SPONSOR ME! SPONSOR ME!

08:30.134 --> 08:31.844
{\an1}OK. HERE.

08:31.928 --> 08:35.389
{\an1}TAKE IT.

08:39.519 --> 08:40.770
SPONSOR ME!

08:42.938 --> 08:44.190
GWAA.

08:48.319 --> 08:49.987
SPONSOR ME!

08:55.826 --> 08:58.246
SPONSOR ME!

08:58.329 --> 08:59.705
OOH.

08:59.789 --> 09:02.583
[GRUNTING]

09:02.667 --> 09:04.710
{\an1}I DIDN'T KNOW WHAT
CAPTAIN HERO WAS UP TO,

09:04.794 --> 09:06.671
{\an1}SO I NEEDED
TO RUN SOME TESTS.

09:10.383 --> 09:13.302
I WAS AFRAID OF THIS.

09:13.386 --> 09:15.680
STEROIDS.

09:18.641 --> 09:19.600
{\an1}CLARA?

09:19.684 --> 09:22.812
WOOLDOOR. WHEN
DID YOU GET OUT?

09:22.895 --> 09:24.814
CLARA, THE ONLY THING

09:24.897 --> 09:27.650
{\an4}THAT GOT ME THROUGH MY TIME
IN THE MALL SECURITY-SLASH-
LOST AND FOUND LOUNGE

09:27.733 --> 09:31.821
WAS THINKING ABOUT YOU
AND OUR LEMONADE STAND.

09:31.904 --> 09:33.656
WELL, I, UH...

09:33.739 --> 09:35.324
EVENING, OLD-TIMER.

09:35.408 --> 09:37.034
OH. WHAT? WOOLDOOR?

09:37.118 --> 09:38.160
HUH?

09:40.121 --> 09:41.205
[GASPS]

09:44.166 --> 09:47.211
AWKWARD!

09:47.295 --> 09:49.213
{\an5}WOOLDOOR, LISTEN.
I DIDN'T KNOW
HOW LONG YOU'D BE IN--

09:49.297 --> 09:52.675
HOW COULD YOU GUYS?

09:52.758 --> 09:54.510
HOW COULD YOU?

09:54.593 --> 09:58.180
{\an1}[SOBBING]

09:58.264 --> 09:59.473
{\an1}Foxxy: CAPTAIN HERO
WAS IN TROUBLE.

09:59.557 --> 10:02.268
{\an1}SO WE DECIDED TO STAGE
AN INTERVENTION.

10:02.351 --> 10:05.021
EVERYBODY READY?

10:05.938 --> 10:09.608
OH, YOU MUST BE HERE
TO SEE CAPTAIN HERO,

10:09.692 --> 10:13.904
{\an1}'CAUSE YOU ARE A 12-YEAR-OLD
GIRL AND A DONKEY.

10:13.988 --> 10:17.700
REALLY? MATTHEW BRODERICK AND
SARAH JESSICA PARKER ARE HERE?

10:17.783 --> 10:19.952
HEY, WHAT GIVES?

10:20.036 --> 10:23.414
HERO, WE ALL KNOW
YOU'RE ABUSING STEROIDS,

10:23.497 --> 10:25.458
AND WE'RE WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

10:25.541 --> 10:26.876
WE LOVE YOU.

10:35.134 --> 10:38.220
ANYWAY,
ADDICTION IS DANGEROUS,

10:38.304 --> 10:40.389
WHETHER IT'S DRUGS
OR LOTTERY TICKETS

10:40.473 --> 10:42.558
OR SUPER LOTTO
OR MEGAPLAY JACKPOT

10:42.641 --> 10:45.978
{\an5}OR TRIPLE SCRATCH LOT--
GODDAMN, I GOT TO GET
SOME LOTTERY TICKETS.

10:46.062 --> 10:48.689
{\an1}I'M GONNA WIN BIG THIS TIME.
I CAN FEEL IT.

10:48.773 --> 10:49.815
THIS IS NONSENSE.

10:49.899 --> 10:53.069
{\an4}THE ONLY THING
I'M ADDICTED TO
IS FIGHTING CRIME,

10:53.152 --> 10:56.364
MAKING LISTS OF 3s...

10:56.447 --> 10:59.408
{\an1}BE THAT AS IT MAY,
STEROIDS CAUSE CANCER,

10:59.492 --> 11:02.078
{\an4}KIDNEY FAILURE,
HEART PROBLEMS,
HOME RUN RECORDS.

11:02.161 --> 11:06.332
{\an5}AND ON OCCASION,
THEY'VE BEEN KNOWN
TO CAUSE FITS OF RAGE.

11:06.415 --> 11:09.585
{\an1}FITS OF RAGE?
I'LL SHOW YOU FITS OF RAGE.

11:09.668 --> 11:11.253
AGGGH!

11:18.094 --> 11:22.807
{\an4}YES, I KNOW
THE GANG'S HEARTS
WERE IN THE RIGHT PLACE,

11:22.890 --> 11:26.560
{\an4}BUT SURPRISING ME
WITH AN INTERVENTION
WAS JUST WRONG.

11:26.644 --> 11:27.770
AHHHHH!

11:27.853 --> 11:30.940
{\an1}OK, MAYBE I DO HAVE
A BIG PROBLEM,

11:31.023 --> 11:33.651
{\an4}BUT THERE'S A RIGHT WAY
AND A WRONG WAY TO TALK
ABOUT THESE THINGS.

11:33.734 --> 11:38.489
{\an1}IT'S SUCH A DRAG
LIVING WITH ROOMMATES.

11:38.572 --> 11:40.699
AGGGH!

11:40.783 --> 11:43.619
I DON'T NEED THIS PLACE.
I DON'T NEED ANY OF YOU.

11:43.702 --> 11:45.246
YOU'RE ALL DEAD TO ME.

11:45.329 --> 11:47.540
HOO-HA, HOO-HA.

11:47.623 --> 11:50.000
{\an1}HOO! HOO! HOO!
WAH! WAH! AHH! AHH! AHH!

11:50.084 --> 11:52.128
[POP]

11:52.211 --> 11:53.546
[CROWD CHEERING]

11:53.629 --> 11:56.048
[ORGAN PLAYS "CHARGE"]

11:57.383 --> 11:58.300
{\an1}THE DUDE
AT THE NUTRITION STORE

11:58.384 --> 12:01.303
{\an1}GAVE ME AN ADDRESS
FOR THIS PLACE I COULD GO,

12:01.387 --> 12:04.265
{\an4}A PLACE HE SAID
WHERE I COULD BE
WITH PEOPLE LIKE MYSELF.

12:04.348 --> 12:06.725
AH-GA-GA-GA-GA.

12:06.809 --> 12:08.727
I HAVE NOWHERE ELSE TO GO.

12:08.811 --> 12:11.147
{\an1}MY FRIENDS
JUST DON'T GET ME.

12:11.230 --> 12:12.440
I GETS YA.

12:12.523 --> 12:14.525
{\an1}AS LONG AS YOU DON'T
GETS WITH ME OLIVE OYL.

12:14.608 --> 12:17.486
SHE'S MY NUMBER-ONE GOYL.

12:17.570 --> 12:19.613
{\an1}GET YOUR SKINNY ASS
OUT THERE AND EARN, BITCH.

12:19.697 --> 12:22.575
{\an1}OOH, LOOK AT
ALL THE MUS-CLES.

12:22.658 --> 12:24.702
I CAN HOOKS YOU UP, CAP'N.

12:24.785 --> 12:28.414
{\an5}I JUST SCORED SOME
GREAT ROIDS FROM
THE JOLLY GREEN GIANT.

12:28.497 --> 12:29.832
SWEET.

12:29.915 --> 12:33.169
{\an1}YOU'VE GOT SOME
CREAMED SPINACH ON YOUR CHEEK.

12:33.252 --> 12:36.005
OH. THAT'S NOT SPINACH.

12:36.088 --> 12:37.548
HA-HA-GA-GA-GA!

12:37.631 --> 12:39.049
[SOBBING]

12:39.133 --> 12:42.845
{\an1}I WAS FINALLY IN A PLACE
WHERE NO ONE WOULD JUDGE ME,

12:42.928 --> 12:44.513
EXCEPT MAYBE JUDGE FUDGE.

12:44.597 --> 12:46.515
I'D NEVER JUDGE YOU, BABY.

12:46.599 --> 12:49.977
I'M FAR TOO BUSY
BEING DELICIOUS.

12:50.060 --> 12:52.188
{\an1}EVERYONE HAD
MOVED ON WITHOUT ME.

12:52.271 --> 12:55.191
{\an4}THERE WAS NO PLACE
IN THE MODERN WORLD
FOR WOOLDOOR SOCKBAT.

12:55.274 --> 12:59.153
{\an4}I HAD TO GET BACK
TO THE ONLY PLACE
THAT MADE ANY SENSE TO ME--

12:59.236 --> 13:01.614
{\an1}THE MALL SECURITY-SLASH-
LOST AND FOUND LOUNGE.

13:06.285 --> 13:08.120
OOPS. THAT'S NOT RIGHT.

